Regarding ∆s, positive values were defined as an anteriorly directed movement, i.e. protrusion, whereas negative values indicated a retrusion. Total sagittal changes were composed of translational (∆s(translation)), i.e. a bodily movement, of the incisor in sagittal direction, and tipping movements (∆s(tipping)), resulting in the following formulae for the upper and lower jaw, respectively.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
