Alterations of the incisal point in the vertical direction were measured perpendicularly to the occlusal plane (OcP), passing through half overbite and the occlusal contact of the most distal tooth. Positive values of ∆v were defined by movements of the incisal point away from OcP, i.e. intrusion, whereas negative values expressed incisor extrusion. Applying trigonometry, the following two equations were established to compute ∆v for the upper and lower jaw, respectively, based on cephalometric analysis (Fig. 1):\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
